Subject:Re: [EVDL] Best EV Tires
I used to keep a keen eye on my regular commute with my 2002 Prius
and noticed that I took about 5% MPG hit at the moment that I
replaced the tires. I started inquiring and found out that this
is usual - new tires have more friction due to the thicker layer
of rubber that is compressing and expanding and thus generating
heat from movement, hence more loss. With the wearing down
(and stiffening from aging) tires get lower in rolling resistance.

Cor van de Water
Chief Scientist
Proxim Wireless Corporation http://www.proxim.com
