Subject: Re: [EVDL] Best EV Tires

I don't have a lot of data, but have tried two types of tires.

On my ICE (2000 Mazda 626 V6) I have the Michelin Energy Saver A/S.
.Those tires (running at sidewall max pressure) gained at least 5% MPG
compared to my previous tires (Toyo Z800 Ultras well worn).  I really
like those tires and would have gotten the same tires for my EV if the
rim and tire size I needed was available.  On those tires, it feels like
the Mazda can coast forever.  They are also wearing very well.

My EV has Pirelli P6 LRR all-season tires.  They also seem to be wearing
very well.  The EV doesn't coast as well, but I don't think it's the
tires.  I have a slight brake drag on both front wheels that I haven't
been able to find.

Mike

